bibl.title: George W. Anderson vs. J. C. Mitchell. Return from Sheriff
bibl.note: Our transcription is based on a digital image of the microfilmed original.

div1.p: I do hereby return to the Hon. C. H. Hanford Chief Justice of Washington Territory and Judge of the 3rd Judicial District thereof, that before the coming to me of the accused writ the said George W. Anderson was committed to my custody, and is detained by virtue of another writ, a copy of which is thereto accused; the original of which I also herewith produce: and herintherof I have the body of the said George W. Anderson before you at the day and place within mentioned, as therein commanded, J H McGraw, Sheriff King County W. T.

Territory of Washington County of King ss. JH McGraw, the Sheriff of said County, who makes the above return, being duly sworn, say that the same is true. Subscribed and sworn to before me the 2nd day of October 1889 R M Hopkins Clerk.
